                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310908-229-off1173 t18310908-229-victim1705"></join>
                  </persName>
            .</p>
               <p>JOHN CORNELIOUS. I live with my parents, in Field-lane, Holborn. On Saturday, the 2nd of July, I was in <placeName id="t18310908-229-crimeloc1175">Gray's Inn-lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18310908-229-crimeloc1175" type="placeName" value="Gray's Inn-lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18310908-229-crimeloc1175" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310908-229-off1173 t18310908-229-crimeloc1175"></join>, selling water-cresses - I saw the prisoner go to Mr. Nichols' shop, and pull down a piece of print, tuck it under her clothes, and walk away - I told the shopman; he followed her, and took hold of her arm - she then dropped the cotton.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310908-229-person1706">
                  WILLIAM 
                  WOOD
               <interp inst="t18310908-229-person1706" type="surname" value="WOOD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-229-person1706" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-229-person1706" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was shopman to the prosecutor. In consequence of what I heard I went and stopped the prisoner in Fox-court, and the cotton fell from her clothes - she walked back with me a little way, then dragged herself from me; she got into a passion, and struck me several times, with such violence as to make me let her go - when she got into Gravel-lane the Police-officer came up, and took her.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310908-229-person1707">
                  HUGH 
                  CASH
               <interp inst="t18310908-229-person1707" type="surname" value="CASH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-229-person1707" type="given" value="HUGH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-229-person1707" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I received charge of the prisoner; I saw her strike the witness very violently, and her hands were bleeding; I took her to the watch-house - she wanted to make it up, and said she knew what she had done, that she had been guilty of shoplifting, and she should be committed to Newgate - I did not perceive she was intoxicated.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I picked up the cotton, but I was a little in liquor, or I should not have done so.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18310908-229-verdict1176" type="verdictDescription">
